#### Removals:
- **Druids:** Primal Savagery
- **Death Knights:** Deathwyrm's Fury
- **Mages:** Conjure Elemental, Flurry
- **Shamans:** Antimagic Field, Prismatic Spray

#### Unassigned:
- Lightning Charged (should be artificer)

### Spell-Specific Changes
- Amplify or Dampen Magic renamed to Amplify/Dampen Magic, to match Enlarge/Reduce. Also lets it fit on one line in the spell lists.
- Arcane Barrage no longer requires an attack roll. Damage reduced from a max of 15d4 to 10d4. Knockback effect now tied to secondary Strength save, max knockback reduced from 30 feet to 20. Damage now increases by 2d4 per spell slot level.
- Arcane Blast no longer require a Dexterity save. Base damage changed to 1d4 + spellcasting ability modifier, increasing by 2d4.
- Army of the Dead changed to Silverblade's version.
- Bloodlust and Heroism drops the "and Heroism" part of its name, to avoid confusion with the existing spell.
- Cataclysm: hopefully cleared up [Issue #808](https://github.com/WC5E/Warcraft-5e-Conversion/issues/808) on the github by removing the word "spell" from the line "A creature who takes fire damage from this spell--"
- Conjure Undead (formerly known as Summon Undead) no longer allows you to choose which undead type you summon, like other conjure spells.
- Deathwyrm's Fury spell removed.
- Dominate Undead renamed to Control Undead, reworked so that it doesn't apply the charmed condition and therefore isn't functionally useless. Based on the conversation in [Issue #806](https://github.com/WC5E/Warcraft-5e-Conversion/issues/806).
- Eclipse altered. No longer references Elune and An'she, requires concentration, max duration increased to 8 hours, and reworded how darkness appears.
- Flurry spell removed.
- Lunar Strike no longer requires a saving throw. Damage changed to 1d4 to initial target (+1d4 if in moonlight) and half damage to all creatures in an AoE. 
- Mind blast reduced from d10 to d8 damage.
- Shadow bolt now always deals d12 damage with no optional self-damage component. Instead, you take 1 damage per 12 rolled on a die.

\pagebreak

## Design Notes
- Force damage spells that don't require saves to deal damage are designed to deal 25% less damage than average (using the rule of "spells that deal no damage on a successful save deal 25% more" from the DMG).
- Death Knights and Druids get poison damage spells. DKs because of plague, druids because of animal venom.

### Chaos "Element"
 Does not deal a predetermined damage type, instead rolling a d8 on a table to choose an element: acid, cold, fire, force, lightning, poison, psychic, or thunder. Typically has two different sets of damage dice (such as 2d8 + 2d6), where you choose one of the d8s for damage type. If the same number is rolled twice on one of the dice sets, an additional effect occurs.

##### Chaos Element Spells
Level   | Spells
--------|:-------:
Cantrip |✦ Touch of Chaos
1st     |Chaos Bolt ^XGE^
2nd     |
3rd     |✦ Chaos Aura, ✦ Chaos Wave
4th     |
5th     |✦ Chaos Breach

**[Due to being incomplete, chaos spells are not integrated at this time. See next page for sketched ideas.]**

