#### Chaos Aura
*3rd-level evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self (15 feet)
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___
You create a roiling aura of chaotic energies that stretches from you in a 15-foot radius. Until the spell ends, the aura moves with you, centered on you. 

Whenever another creature ends its turn in the aura or enters it for the first time on a turn, they must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes 3d8 + 2d6 damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one. Choose one of the d8s whenever you deal damage. The number rolled on that die determines the type of the damage dealt, as shown below.

d8 |Damage Type |d8 |Damage Type
---|------------|---|-----------
1  | Acid		| 5 | Lightning
2  | Cold		| 6 | Poison
3  | Fire		| 7 | Psychic
4  | Force		| 8 | Thunder

**[Double die effect.]**

**[Can use a BA to buff other chaos spells? Can roll more d8s for sake of choosing damage types?]**

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the spell deals an additional 1d6 damage for each slot level above 3rd.

#### Chaos Breach
*5th-level evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___
You launch an intense beam of chaotic energies at a target within range. The target must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 4d8 + 5d6 damage, or half as much on a successful saving throw. Choose one of the d8s. The number rolled on that die determines the spell's damage type, as shown below.

d8 |Damage Type |d8 |Damage Type
---|------------|---|-----------
1  | Acid		| 5 | Lightning
2  | Cold		| 6 | Poison
3  | Fire		| 7 | Psychic
4  | Force		| 8 | Thunder

If you roll the same number on both d8s, the spell deals an additional 2d8 damage to the target. Choose one of the d8s to determine the new damage type. This effect repeats until two different numbers are rolled.

Until the end of your next turn (including against this spell), the target is more susceptible to the spell's initial damage type. If the creature has immunity to this damage type, it is reduced to resistance, and if it has resistance, it is suppressed for the duration.

\columnbreak

#### Chaos Wave
*3rd-level evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self (30-foot cone)
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___
You release a wave of chaotic energy in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a saving throw or take 2d8 + 2d6 damage and suffer an additional effect. A successful save results in half damage and no other effect. Choose one of the d6s and one of the d8s for each target. The number rolled on the d6 determines the spell's saving throw and additional effect and the number rolled on the d8 determines the spell's damage type, as shown below.

d6| Saving Throw | Additional Effect
--|--------------|---------
1 | Strength     | Pushed away from you a number of feet equal to 1d4 x 5. 
2 | Dexterity    | Knocked prone.
3 | Constitution | Stunned until the end of its next turn.
4 | Intelligence | Subtract 1d4 from the next saving throw it makes before the end of your next turn.
5 | Wisdom       | Takes an additional 1d10 force damage.
6 | Charisma     | Subtract 1d4 from the next attack roll it makes before the end of your next turn.

**[Note that the above effects were pulled from a different homebrew. Some are clearly better than others, so needs to be reworked.]**

d8 |Damage Type |d8 |Damage Type
---|------------|---|-----------
1  | Acid		| 5 | Lightning
2  | Cold		| 6 | Poison
3  | Fire		| 7 | Psychic
4  | Force		| 8 | Thunder


\pagebreakNum

#### Mass Teleport
*9th-level conjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 minute
- **Range:** 300 feet
- **Components:** V, M (expensive component, consumed)
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
---
This spell instantly transports you and any number of willing creatures and/or objects of your choice that you can see within range to a destination you select. All creatures and objects must be able to fit entirely inside a 300-foot cube. You can designate creatures and objects you cannot see as targets as long as they are within an object you can see; for example, creatures inside a building.

The destination you choose must be known to you, and it must be on the same plane of existence as you. Your familiarity with the destination determines whether you arrive there successfully. The DM rolls d100 and consults the table.

##### Teleportation
| Familiarity | Mishap | Similar Area | Off Target | On Target |
|---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| Associated object | — | — | — | 01–100 |
| Very familiar | 01–05 | 06–13 | 14–24 | 25–100 |
| Seen casually | 01–33 | 34–43 | 44–53 | 54–100 |
| Viewed once | 01–43 | 44–53 | 54–73 | 74–100 |
| Description | 01–43 | 44–53 | 54–73 | 74–100 |
| False destination | 01–50 | 51–100 | — | — |

***Familiarity.*** "Associated object" means that you possess an object taken from the desired destination within the last six months, such as a book from a wizard's library, bed linen from a royal suite, or a chunk of marble from a lich's secret tomb.

"Very familiar" is a place you have been very often, a place you have carefully studied, or a place you can see when you cast the spell. "Seen casually" is someplace you have seen more than once but with which you aren't very familiar. "Viewed once" is a place you have seen once, possibly using magic. "Description" is a place whose location and appearance you know through someone else's description, perhaps from a map.

"False destination" is a place that doesn't exist. Perhaps you tried to scry an enemy's sanctum but instead viewed an illusion, or you are attempting to teleport to a familiar location that no longer exists.

***On Target.*** You and your group (or the target object) appear where you want to.

***Off Target.*** You and your group (or the target object) appear a random distance away from the destination in a random direction. Distance off target is 1d10 × 1d10 percent of the distance that was to be traveled. For example, if you tried to travel 120 miles, landed off target, and rolled a 5 and 3 on the two d10s, then you would be off target by 15 percent, or 18 miles. The DM determines the direction off target randomly by rolling a d8 and designating 1 as north, 2 as northeast, 3 as east, and so on around the points of the compass. If you were teleporting to a coastal city and wound up 18 miles out at sea, you could be in trouble.

***Similar Area.*** You and your group (or the target object) wind up in a different area that's visually or thematically similar to the target area. If you are heading for your home laboratory, for example, you might wind up in another wizard's laboratory or in an alchemical supply shop that has many of the same tools and implements as your laboratory. Generally, you appear in the closest similar place, but since the spell has no range limit, you could conceivably wind up anywhere on the plane.

***Mishap.*** The spell's unpredictable magic results in a difficult journey. Each teleporting creature (or the target object) takes 3d10 force damage, and the DM rerolls on the table to see where you wind up (multiple mishaps can occur, dealing damage each time).
